Description:
    Generate a TypeScript Stimulus controller and automatically integrate it with the application.

    This generator creates:
    - A TypeScript Stimulus controller file in app/javascript/controllers/
    - Automatically imports the controller in controllers/index.ts
    - Registers the controller with the Stimulus application
    - Updates .cursorrules with generation information

Example:
    rails generate stimulus_controller modal

    This will create:
        app/javascript/controllers/modal_controller.ts
        
    And update:
        app/javascript/controllers/index.ts (adds import and registration)
        .cursorrules (adds generation notes)

    The controller will be available in HTML as:
        data-controller="modal"

Usage:
    rails generate stimulus_controller NAME

Arguments:
    NAME    The name of the Stimulus controller (snake_case)

Examples:
    rails generate stimulus_controller dropdown
    rails generate stimulus_controller form_validator  
    rails generate stimulus_controller image_gallery

Generated controller features:
    - TypeScript support with proper typing
    - Basic controller structure with connect/disconnect
    - Placeholder for targets, values, and classes
    - Console logging for debugging
    - Ready-to-use template with common patterns
